performUpkeep.t.sol
├─ given the contract is paused
│  └─ it should revert
└─ given the contract is not paused
   ├─ when the asset out params are not set
   │  └─ it should revert
   └─ when the asset out params are set
      ├─ when there are eligible assets and the asset out price is not valid
      │  └─ it should revert
      └─ when there are eligible assets and the asset out price is valid
         ├─ when an eligible asset params are not set
         │  └─ it should revert
         └─ when the eligible asset params are set
            ├─ when the eligible asset has a live auction
            │  └─ it should revert
            └─ when the eligible asset does not have a live auction
               ├─ when the eligible asset amount is below the minimum auction size
               │  └─ it should revert
               └─ when the eligible asset amount is above the minimum auction size
                  ├─ when ending auctions with a stale asset out price
                  │  └─ it should end the auction
                  └─ when an auction is ended
                     ├─ when the ended auction is not live
                     │  └─ it should revert
                     └─ when the ended auction is live
                        └─ given the fee aggregator is set to the auction contract
                           └─ it should only perform a single transfer of asset out to the receiver
